Class QueueImpl

  • java.lang.Object

    public class QueueImpl
extends Object
implements Queue
    Implementation of a Queue

    Completely non blocking between adding to queue and delivering to consumers.

    Author:
    Tim Fox, Andy Taylor, Jeff Mesnil, Clebert Suconic

      • setConsumersRefCount

        public void setConsumersRefCount(org.apache.activemq.utils.ReferenceCounter referenceCounter)
        Description copied from interface: Queue
        This will set a reference counter for every consumer present on the queue. The ReferenceCounter will know what to do when the counter became zeroed. This is used to control what to do with temporary queues, especially on shared subscriptions where the queue needs to be deleted when all the consumers are closed.
        Specified by:
